{"_response_info":{"status":"ok"},"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/giving-staff-time-off-for-magistrate-duty.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/giving-staff-time-off-for-magistrate-duty","title":"Giving staff time off for magistrate duty","format":"answer","updated_at":"2012-10-22T15:14:58+00:00","details":{"need_id":"B113","business_proposition":true,"description":"How to give an employee time off to volunteer as a magistrate, and how much time they are allowed off","language":"en","body":"\n<div class=\"summary\">\n<p>You must, by law, allow an employee who is a magistrate reasonable time off work to carry out their duties.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Your employee will have to be in court at least 13 days, or 26 half-days a year.</p>\n\n<p>They’ll get their magistrate rota well in advance, so you’ll have plenty of time to plan and agree the time off.</p>\n\n<p>You don&rsquo;t have to pay employees for their magistrate work, but many employers do.</p>\n\n<p>If you don’t pay them, they can claim an <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.magistrates-association.org.uk/allowances.php\" title=\"allowance\">allowance</a> from the court for loss of earnings.</p>\n\n<h2>Scotland</h2>\n\n<p>You must give time off to an employee who is a <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.scotland.gov.uk/Topics/Justice/legal/criminalprocedure/justice-peace/d/IssuestoConsider/Timeoffworkandremuner\" title=\"Time off for a Justice of the Peace in Scotland\">Justice of the Peace in Scotland.</a></p>\n","alternative_title":""},"tags":[{"title":"Statutory leave and time off","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/employing-people%2Ftime-off.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes maternity and paternity leave, holiday entitlement and sick pay","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=employing-people%2Ftime-off","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/employing-people/time-off"},"parent":{"title":"Employing people","id":"https://